      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky and the betting will be instructive. The Blacker yard has accepted with three. BEWICKED (4) is the one with race experience. Led and held on to place in a small field here a month ago, and she's won an Elwick trial over 800m since. Will have come on, and she sets the standard. The betting should be a good guide to the relative ability of the debutants. FARMER'S SON (1) was placed in his latest trial and Johnstone sticks from that, and he looks ready to run well. ZALAU (3) has prepared well and maps for the softest run. OFFA MORE (6) and FIERCE SPIRIT (2) both present on debut for the Blacker yard and profile well. The former has the top hoop aboard.",
